(
  'Beach Clubs and Sunset Bars: Calvia''s Best Evening Spots',
  'beach-clubs-sunset-bars-calvia-best-evening-spots',
  'From chilled sunset cocktails at Portals to lively beach clubs in Magaluf, here is where to spend your evenings along Calvia''s coast.',
  '<p>Calvia''s coastline stretches for over 50 kilometers, and along it you will find some of Mallorca''s most atmospheric spots for evening drinks. Whether you prefer a tranquil sunset with a glass of local wine or a vibrant beach club with international DJs, the municipality delivers on every front.</p>

<h2>Sunset Cocktails: The Best Views</h2>
<p>Gran Folies in Cala Llamp offers what many consider the most dramatic sunset viewing on the island. Perched on rocks above crystal-clear water, the bar serves expertly mixed cocktails as the sun drops into the Mediterranean. Arrive at least an hour before sunset to secure a front-row spot. The atmosphere is sophisticated but relaxed, attracting an international crowd who appreciate the natural spectacle.</p>
<p>Puro Beach near Palmanova combines a beach club ambiance with a genuine focus on quality cocktails and food. The Balinese-inspired decor, curated music, and attentive service create an experience that justifies the premium pricing. Their sunset sessions with live acoustic music on Thursdays are particularly special.</p>

<h2>Lively Beach Clubs</h2>
<p>Nikki Beach in Magaluf has brought its global brand of glamorous beach club culture to Calvia. Expect poolside DJs, champagne sprays, and a see-and-be-seen crowd. The food program is surprisingly strong, with sushi and Mediterranean plates that hold their own against standalone restaurants. Weekend brunches are the signature event.</p>

<h2>Wine Bars and Local Gems</h2>
<p>For something more intimate, El Peso in Calvia village is a wine bar specializing in Mallorcan and Spanish natural wines. The stone-walled interior and candlelit terrace make it ideal for a quieter evening. The owner is passionate about island producers and can guide you through an education in Mallorcan wine over the course of a delightful evening.</p>
<p>Vinatea in Santa Ponsa offers an extensive by-the-glass selection with knowledgeable staff and excellent cheese and charcuterie boards. It is a neighborhood spot that feels like a discovery every time you visit.</p>

<h2>Planning Your Evening</h2>
<p>The classic Calvia evening starts with sunset drinks at a coastal spot, followed by a late dinner around 9:30 or 10pm. Reservations are essential at popular venues from June through September. Off-season visits, October and May, offer the same beauty with far fewer crowds and often lower prices.</p>',
